ResourceHeader.Description: GUMICS (Grand Unified Magnetosphere Ionosphere Coupling simulation) is a 3-dimensional computer simulation developed at the FMI which used to model the plasma environment of the near-Earth space. The simulation covers most of the regime dominated by the Earth's magnetic field (the magnetosphere), and some parts of the solar wind. The magnetospheric domain is coupled to another computer code describing the ionosphere, which is the ionized upper atmosphere. See http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.jastp.2012.03.006 for the details of the used version (GUMICS-4).
ResourceHeader.Acknowledgement: We request that the user contacts the HYB and GUMICS simulation developers before publishing or presenting results from these simulation codes. We request that the user offers co-authorship for the developers and acknowledgements for the original model. Contacts at the Finnish Meteorological Institute are Riku Jarvinen (riku.jarvinen@fmi.fi) for the HYB simulation and Minna Palmroth (minna.palmroth@fmi.fi) for the GUMICS simulation. HYB references: http://hwa.fmi.fi/hyb/refs.php GUMICS references: http://gumics.fmi.fi/references/

SimulationDomain.GridStructure: Variable. 5 levels. GridCellSize gives the size of the smallest grid cell.

Property.Name: Inner boundary altitude from the center of the Earth
Property.Description: Altitude below the magnetic field is assumed to be undisturbed dipolar magnetic field.

InputField.Name: IMF
InputField.Description: Interplanetary Magnetic Field

InputField.Name: Center_Dipole_Field
InputField.Description: A dipolar magnetic field located at the center of the object. Field Value corresponds to the magnitude of magnetic moment vector in T/m^3 of the dipole in the GSE coordinate system.

Property.Name: Solar UV Flux @ 10.7
Tilt angle on the xz plane
Property.Description: Tilt angle of the Earth’s magnetic dipole on the GSE xz-plane. Positive when the Northern hemisphere points toward the Sun.

Property.Name: Tilt angle on the yz plane
Property.Description: Tilt angle of the Earth’s magnetic dipole on the GSE yz-plane. The angle increases clockwise when viewed from the Sun.

SimulationDomain.GridStructure: Variable. 5 levels. GridCellSize gives the size of the smallest grid cell.

Property.Name: Inner boundary altitude from the center of the Earth
Property.Description: Altitude below the magnetic field is assumed to be undisturbed dipolar magnetic field.

InputField.Name: IMF
InputField.Description: Interplanetary Magnetic Field

InputField.Name: Center_Dipole_Field
InputField.Description: A dipolar magnetic field located at the center of the object. Field Value corresponds to the magnitude of magnetic moment vector in T/m^3 of the dipole in the GSE coordinate system.
